# gen199, Italian probe: the SAME Python F3 semantics reached through the Italian
# eval cue ("cosa restituisce" / "cosa ritorna"). One evaluator, two natural
# languages AND two programming languages meeting at one code path — the bilingual
# ratchet over the language-as-delta engine (CODE-MASTERY §7b).
> cosa restituisce add(2, 3): def add(a, b): return a + b
< I read it as code and worked it out: add(2, 3) returns 5.
> cosa ritorna f(2, 3, 4): def f(a, b, c): return a + b * c
< I read it as code and worked it out: f(2, 3, 4) returns 14.